40:16.858 --> 40:20.470
I'm gonna sell off my IRAs, okay?
I'll have it in 10 days.

40:20.634 --> 40:22.009
I can't do margin.

40:22.330 --> 40:23.638
I need cash.

40:23.737 --> 40:26.551
I'm in Jersey right now.
Where am I gonna get cash?

40:26.617 --> 40:29.169
I'm sure one of those chemical plants
has an ATM machine.

40:29.241 --> 40:31.794
All right, look. I'll get the cash.
Just put in the order.

40:31.865 --> 40:33.359
Cash by Tuesday.

40:33.433 --> 40:35.287
I'll bring it to you personally on Monday.

40:35.352 --> 40:37.075
Don't punk out on me.

40:39.191 --> 40:40.401
- Hey.
- Hey.

40:40.535 --> 40:42.425
What are you doing here?

40:42.905 --> 40:45.719
I feel like we didn't get off
on the right foot yesterday...

40:45.784 --> 40:47.726
so I thought maybe...

40:47.800 --> 40:50.733
I'd come here and take you to lunch.
Maybe we could bond a little.

40:50.806 --> 40:55.029
I think we bonded just fine around 3:10 this
morning when your knee was in my crotch.

40:55.096 --> 40:56.372
Right.

40:56.792 --> 40:58.003
I'll buy.

40:59.319 --> 41:01.075
- You want to buy me lunch?
- Yeah.

41:01.143 --> 41:05.201
I figured it's the proper thing to do
after sleeping with each other.

41:08.887 --> 41:09.934
Okay.

41:14.135 --> 41:17.003
- So, nice bank.
- I'm glad you like it.

41:18.039 --> 41:22.130
I like the small-town feel.
It's less complicated.

41:22.197 --> 41:25.132
Somebody needs money,
they just come in and say:

41:25.844 --> 41:27.733
"Percy, I need a loan."

41:28.149 --> 41:29.294
Right?

41:30.614 --> 41:33.712
And then, of course, you say,
"Well, yeah. How much?"

41:33.973 --> 41:37.769
They say, "I don't know.
You tell me. $50,000?"

41:38.164 --> 41:40.018
What, you need $50,000?

41:40.531 --> 41:42.442
- Do I need $50,000?
- Yeah.

41:43.541 --> 41:46.159
No. I most assuredly do not.

41:46.837 --> 41:49.040
I was just admiring the process.

41:57.748 --> 42:00.879
How many cylinders does a NASCAR engine
have, six or eight?

42:00.946 --> 42:02.223
- How...
- Yeah.

42:02.292 --> 42:04.624
Six... or eight...

42:07.154 --> 42:11.911
depending on the gas mileage
consumption of the automobile.

42:12.083 --> 42:15.857
You never worked in the pit at NASCAR.
You might as well admit it.

42:16.626 --> 42:18.863
All right, you know, fine.

42:21.074 --> 42:23.757
I never really had an aptitude for engines.

42:23.825 --> 42:25.417
Jay... Jeff...

42:26.194 --> 42:29.839
Jeff Gordon didn't really trust me
in the pit that much.

42:30.353 --> 42:31.947
But you did drive the cars.

42:32.050 --> 42:33.456
- Drive?
- Yeah.

42:33.873 --> 42:35.815
- Absolutely.
- Good.

42:56.815 --> 42:59.717
All right! Fine! I never drove NASCAR!

43:00.111 --> 43:02.598
But I was nervous
and I wanted to impress you.

43:02.671 --> 43:04.560
You shouldn't have lied.

43:05.423 --> 43:09.197
All right. This is the deal.
We go one lap around.

43:09.902 --> 43:12.521
If you beat me, I'll loan you the money.

43:14.829 --> 43:18.344
- Really?
- I knew it! I knew you needed the money.

43:18.414 --> 43:20.235
I don't need the money!

43:47.629 --> 43:49.155
Move over!

43:55.501 --> 43:57.474
Yeah. Fool!

44:10.730 --> 44:11.875
Sucker!

44:51.720 --> 44:53.061
Move it, man!

44:54.985 --> 44:57.024
What the hell are you doing?

45:03.783 --> 45:07.524
- I think it's obvious who came in first.
- You're doggone right. You know I won.

45:07.878 --> 45:12.351
- I was through the bushes before...
- I was through first. I had more speed.

45:12.422 --> 45:14.527
I was through the bushes
and on the asphalt...

45:14.598 --> 45:17.348
- before you even were at the bushes.
- Look.

45:19.335 --> 45:20.992
Dispatch, this is 53 Charlie.

45:21.061 --> 45:24.127
Brian, we got a problem.
Two cars have jumped...

45:27.655 --> 45:29.563
License and registration.

45:33.701 --> 45:36.067
- Poppy!
- There's my beautiful girl.

45:37.412 --> 45:39.203
Simon, I want you to meet my granddad.

45:39.270 --> 45:42.084
- Hi, there. Howard Jones.
- Simon Green. Good to meet you, sir.

45:42.149 --> 45:43.578
Nice to meet you.

45:43.652 --> 45:45.441
- Hey, Speed Racer.
- Hey!

45:45.540 --> 45:48.769
- What's with the white kid?
- That's Simon. He's my boyfriend.

45:48.835 --> 45:51.138
Your boyfriend?
You didn't tell me he was white.

45:51.204 --> 45:52.382
- Yes, I did.
- When?

45:52.452 --> 45:54.427
- Back at the home.
- I thought you was kidding.

45:54.501 --> 45:56.388
Okay. Well, I think that's it.

45:56.803 --> 45:59.191
I think you're forgetting about the vodka.

45:59.266 --> 46:00.827
Say grace, Percy.

46:03.043 --> 46:05.082
Thank you, Lord. Amen.

46:06.914 --> 46:09.534
- That was fast.
- The Lord knows I'm busy.

46:09.731 --> 46:12.697
- Simon, pass on the broccoli, please.
- Yes, sir.

46:12.898 --> 46:16.313
So, what, they don't have any available
young black men in New York anymore?

46:16.386 --> 46:18.457
They just ran out last week, Grandpa.

46:18.530 --> 46:21.978
I'm just trying to figure out
why you chose to go this way.

46:22.050 --> 46:24.254
- Don't mind him.
- It's okay.

46:24.578 --> 46:26.617
My grandmother loved you
when she first met you.

46:26.689 --> 46:29.537
But later she said some things.
I was like, "Wow, Grandma."

46:30.274 --> 46:32.956
- What kind of things?
- Yeah, what kind of things?

46:33.504 --> 46:35.195
Nothing. Just things.

46:35.872 --> 46:37.497
- Such as?
- Yeah, such as?

46:37.568 --> 46:39.609
- Daddy? I got it.
- I know.

46:43.042 --> 46:45.374
You know what?
You're gonna laugh when you hear this.

46:45.440 --> 46:48.735
She said that Theresa was a very pretty girl.

46:50.335 --> 46:52.091
- That's so nice.
- Good taste.

46:52.160 --> 46:55.737
So I ask her
what she liked about you the most, right?

46:55.872 --> 46:57.017
She said...

46:57.088 --> 47:00.797
She says, "I just love
her cute, little, nappy little head."

47:05.758 --> 47:08.661
- Your grandmother, where does she live?
- Brooklyn. Why?

47:08.735 --> 47:12.728
I just wanna know how far I'd have to travel
to kick her old white ass, that's why!

47:12.799 --> 47:14.008
Grandpa.

47:14.238 --> 47:16.344
You don't call my grandchild
no nappy head!

47:16.414 --> 47:19.479
Did she say that while putting on a sheet
for the Klan rally?

47:19.549 --> 47:21.916
Settle down, now! Hand me the butter.

47:21.981 --> 47:24.916
- My grandmother's not a malicious woman.
- No, she's not.

47:24.989 --> 47:27.771
She's 82. She comes from a different time.

47:27.838 --> 47:29.812
I'm 74 and I come from a different time.

47:29.886 --> 47:32.439
You don't hear me calling white folks
honky and flat-ass!

47:32.510 --> 47:33.817
- Casper.
- Cracker.

47:33.884 --> 47:35.313
- Ofay.
- Peckerwood.

47:35.389 --> 47:37.047
- Wonder bread.
- Bird shit.

47:37.115 --> 47:38.263
Bird shit?

47:38.334 --> 47:39.959
It's almost white.

47:40.477 --> 47:41.589
That's pretty good.

47:41.661 --> 47:43.765
Howard. Percy!

47:46.172 --> 47:47.448
It's okay.

47:47.868 --> 47:50.934
I'm really sorry
about what my grandmother said...

47:51.163 --> 47:53.946
but there are some people
you're just never gonna change...

47:54.012 --> 47:55.866
- as much as you'd like to.
- Yep.

47:55.931 --> 47:58.549
I can tell you this. Last Thanksgiving...

47:58.811 --> 48:01.658
my Uncle Dave said a black joke
at the table, right?

48:01.979 --> 48:05.775
So I said, right in front of the whole family,
"Look, that's inappropriate.

48:05.882 --> 48:07.825
"We're not gonna have it."

48:09.402 --> 48:13.264
I think that's how you change people.
You just gotta attack it one at a time.

48:13.338 --> 48:14.352
Exactly.

48:14.426 --> 48:15.953
What was the joke?

48:16.506 --> 48:17.750
Excuse me?

48:19.097 --> 48:20.439
Tell the joke.

48:21.145 --> 48:23.863
- I don't remember it.
- Sure you do. Tell the joke.

48:24.090 --> 48:26.960
- Really, I don't remember it. It was...
- Dad.

48:27.193 --> 48:28.370
Chicken.

48:29.562 --> 48:31.634
- Excuse me?
- I didn't stutter.

48:31.706 --> 48:34.738
Okay, you know what? I'll tell the joke.

48:34.872 --> 48:37.491
- No, Simon. You don't...
- Baby, it's okay.

48:37.754 --> 48:39.181
I'll tell you why.

48:39.257 --> 48:43.250
Because by not telling the joke,
I'm empowering it. Right? So I'll just...

48:44.279 --> 48:47.662
tell the joke and expose
how simple-minded...

48:48.088 --> 48:51.055
and crude and unfunny it actually is.

48:53.208 --> 48:54.898
What do you call...

48:59.798 --> 49:02.930
What do you call 100 black men...

49:03.447 --> 49:05.966
buried in the ground up to their neck?

49:07.192 --> 49:09.166
- What?
- Afro-Turf.

49:12.150 --> 49:14.452
- That's cute.
- What are you laughing at?

49:14.551 --> 49:17.038
- It's cute.
- Cute don't make it funny.

49:17.494 --> 49:18.639
Tell another.

49:18.741 --> 49:21.076
- Dad, no.
- Let the man tell a joke!

49:21.878 --> 49:23.917
I don't know any other ones.

49:25.782 --> 49:30.516
Obviously, I've heard other black jokes,
but I think I've proven my point.

49:30.613 --> 49:33.002
So it's okay to empower the other ones?

49:33.493 --> 49:37.355
Okay. I see what you're doing here,
you're putting me on the spot.

49:37.429 --> 49:40.527
It's okay. Look, it's fine.
'Cause I'm not gonna back down.

49:40.597 --> 49:41.774
Back down, Simon.

49:41.846 --> 49:45.521
The only way to break down barriers
is to have everything out in the open.

49:45.588 --> 49:46.832
- Right?
- Exactly.

49:46.900 --> 49:48.787
So, what do you call...

49:49.556 --> 49:53.353
one black man being chased
by 300 white men?

49:54.131 --> 49:56.618
- What?
- The PGA Tour.

49:58.036 --> 49:59.463
I get it.

49:59.538 --> 50:00.913
Tiger Woods. There it is.

50:01.012 --> 50:02.385
That's good.

50:03.091 --> 50:04.651
Tell another one.

50:07.315 --> 50:10.544
How do we know that Adam and Eve
weren't black?

50:11.538 --> 50:12.486
How?

50:12.562 --> 50:15.629
You ever try to take a rib away
from a black man?

50:18.418 --> 50:19.563
That's pretty good.

50:19.634 --> 50:23.147
- That's pretty good.
- I wouldn't take one from you, I know that!

50:23.218 --> 50:26.415
- You chewing it down to the bone.
- That's a good one.

50:26.769 --> 50:29.998
- He's a rib fan.
- Don't try.

50:30.449 --> 50:31.693
- Tell more.
- Okay.

50:31.761 --> 50:34.063
- Why don't black people like country music?
- Why?

50:34.128 --> 50:38.570
'Cause every time they say "hoe-down,"
they think someone shot their sister.

50:41.841 --> 50:44.141
You gonna be all right?

50:47.024 --> 50:48.551
That is so true.

50:48.656 --> 50:51.787
- That's a tailored joke for you.
- Why I gotta be a ho?

50:51.857 --> 50:53.678
Ain't nobody talking about you.

50:53.744 --> 50:55.434
- It's a sister joke!
- You're sisters.

50:55.504 --> 50:57.097
I'm not the "ho sister."

50:57.168 --> 50:59.501
Come on now. Can't stop now, baby.

50:59.983 --> 51:02.830
What are three things
that a black man can't get?

51:02.895 --> 51:04.999
What is that he can't he get?

51:06.383 --> 51:09.677
A black eye, a fat lip, and a job.

51:15.694 --> 51:18.027
I tell you I'm going to kick this boy's ass!

51:18.094 --> 51:20.777
- Grandpa.
- No, it's...

51:21.486 --> 51:24.781
We know you can take him,
but just sit down. Be nice. Come on.

51:25.806 --> 51:28.740
- Come on, now. It's a joke.
- That's right, Daddy.

51:28.813 --> 51:30.819
Sit down. It's just a joke.

51:31.148 --> 51:33.865
Come on. Hee-hee, ha-ha. That's all it is.

51:37.293 --> 51:39.236
Now if you'll excuse me...

51:39.853 --> 51:41.958
all of a sudden, I lost my appetite.

51:45.515 --> 51:47.337
Think I'll take a walk.

51:56.427 --> 51:59.624
- I should have stopped at "hoe-down."
- You should have never started.

51:59.691 --> 52:02.887
This isn't like us at home,
laughing about this bullshit.

52:02.955 --> 52:04.744
It's my father's house, Simon.

52:04.811 --> 52:07.778
What do you want me to do,
go upstairs and apologize to him again?

52:07.851 --> 52:08.866
No.

52:09.897 --> 52:12.135
Let the storm pass. It'll be fine.

52:13.739 --> 52:15.144
Besides, he dared you!

52:15.210 --> 52:17.348
- He double-dared! He called me chicken.
- I heard!

52:17.417 --> 52:20.713
- I can't be called chicken.
- You have to watch him on those.

52:21.482 --> 52:25.475
You know? I'm fresh out of ideas
as to how to impress your father.

52:26.026 --> 52:29.255
Telling black jokes is never a good idea,
but that's just me.

52:29.322 --> 52:30.598
You think?

52:36.617 --> 52:38.178
I'll talk to him.

52:42.825 --> 52:44.286
Say nice things about me.

52:44.359 --> 52:47.708
No, I'm not going to say nice things
about you. You are still punished.

52:47.816 --> 52:51.647
Baby, I'm a good guy.
I like ribs, too. I don't...

52:54.376 --> 52:56.231
Why are you being so mean to me?

52:56.295 --> 52:58.816
- My grandfather's out there.
- He's not going to come in.

52:58.888 --> 53:01.409
- This is my mom's kitchen!
- She's not going to come in.

53:01.479 --> 53:03.780
You're still gonna do the dishes.

53:05.032 --> 53:07.551
- Get off me.
- Fine, I'll do the dishes.

53:08.038 --> 53:09.980
Here, do the broccoli one.

53:12.903 --> 53:15.771
- Dad, I have to talk to you.
- What?

53:16.102 --> 53:18.916
- Why did you do that?
- I didn't start it. Mr. Nappy Head did.

53:18.981 --> 53:21.600
Dad, Simon's a good man.
He has a good heart.

53:21.670 --> 53:23.809
- A good man?
- You put him on the spot.

53:23.879 --> 53:25.088
