because you saved me from a big heartache.

01:26:31.425 --> 01:26:34.142
Sweetheart, I just don't
understand something.

01:26:34.209 --> 01:26:37.406
- Why did Simon quit his job?
- I don't know. He didn't say.

01:26:37.793 --> 01:26:41.501
Why would a man quit his job on the day
he's gonna meet his future father-in-law?

01:26:41.568 --> 01:26:45.595
Maybe he got tired of waiting
for that promotion that never happened.

01:26:46.882 --> 01:26:48.888
Simon's a rising star, Dad.

01:26:50.272 --> 01:26:52.508
- He really is.
- I believe that.

01:26:53.055 --> 01:26:55.903
But that boss of his is just not a nice man.

01:26:56.384 --> 01:26:58.870
- You ever met him?
- A couple of times.

01:26:59.424 --> 01:27:02.174
He was always friendly, kind of.

01:27:02.944 --> 01:27:06.588
But he always had
this look in his eyes, you know?

01:27:07.968 --> 01:27:09.657
Just not a nice man.

01:27:10.527 --> 01:27:12.829
But he was Simon's mentor, so...

01:27:13.982 --> 01:27:15.192
Whatever.

01:27:16.127 --> 01:27:17.403
Let it go.

01:27:18.336 --> 01:27:20.342
Today is about you and Mom.

01:27:22.910 --> 01:27:25.113
Now, first picture of the night.

01:27:25.181 --> 01:27:27.636
- Let me get my... On my good side.
- Smile.

01:27:29.726 --> 01:27:32.214
I don't want Mom to see me like this.

01:27:34.302 --> 01:27:37.116
- I love you, Dad.
- I love you, too.

01:28:01.147 --> 01:28:02.196
Damn!

01:28:09.083 --> 01:28:10.293
No.

01:28:10.363 --> 01:28:12.185
Do not do this to me, Percy Jones!

01:28:12.251 --> 01:28:16.179
We have a schedule! Tick-tock.
Everything works. Timing.

01:28:16.251 --> 01:28:17.364
I'll be right back.

01:28:17.436 --> 01:28:19.289
- Timing!
- I'll be right back.

01:28:19.388 --> 01:28:21.012
- In 10 minutes?
- Or so, okay?

01:28:21.083 --> 01:28:22.227
How so?

01:28:23.898 --> 01:28:26.766
I'm sorry.
Percy, have you met my wife, Diane?

01:28:27.225 --> 01:28:29.778
I certainly have heard
a lot about you, Percy Jones.

01:28:29.850 --> 01:28:31.312
Nice to meet you.

01:28:31.386 --> 01:28:34.201
- Does Marilyn know you're going AWOL?
- Of course.

01:28:35.289 --> 01:28:37.111
She does not.

01:29:48.532 --> 01:29:50.670
So you missed your train, huh?

01:29:52.981 --> 01:29:56.046
- There's another one at 6:00.
- You gonna be on it?

01:29:56.532 --> 01:29:58.735
I should have been on that one.

01:30:02.356 --> 01:30:04.243
What are you doing here?

01:30:04.532 --> 01:30:06.636
I know why you quit your job.

01:30:07.091 --> 01:30:09.775
You told your boss you was coming here
to meet me and he said:

01:30:09.842 --> 01:30:11.980
"Don't marry that black girl."

01:30:14.802 --> 01:30:17.040
Those weren't exactly the words.

01:30:20.050 --> 01:30:22.636
How did you know we were getting married?

01:30:22.738 --> 01:30:25.901
I told you, son.
Don't nothing get past Percy Jones.

01:30:26.097 --> 01:30:28.203
- Theresa told you.
- That, too.

01:30:31.122 --> 01:30:32.845
Come on, man. Let's get real.

01:30:32.915 --> 01:30:36.230
What you did with your boss
was honorable, impressive...

01:30:37.137 --> 01:30:38.413
and stupid.

01:30:38.482 --> 01:30:42.093
You can't quit your job every time
somebody rolls their eyes at the two of you.

01:30:42.161 --> 01:30:44.202
You'll never make any money.

01:30:51.568 --> 01:30:54.884
- How do you do 25 years?
- Painfully.

01:30:57.807 --> 01:30:59.237
No, seriously.

01:30:59.472 --> 01:31:03.050
If you're gonna marry one of these women,
sometimes it's gonna hurt like hell.

01:31:03.120 --> 01:31:07.526
All you can do is admit that you're wrong
and know that she's always right.

01:31:08.080 --> 01:31:09.573
- She's right?
- That's right.

01:31:09.646 --> 01:31:10.891
- Always?
- Right.

01:31:10.959 --> 01:31:12.169
- Right.
- That's right.

01:31:12.238 --> 01:31:13.515
All right.

01:31:14.063 --> 01:31:16.397
Okay, what about all the talk
about my dignity?

01:31:16.464 --> 01:31:18.984
Do you love her? Do you want her?

01:31:19.822 --> 01:31:21.710
Then she's always right.

01:31:28.461 --> 01:31:31.277
Look, I know I didn't give you a fair shake.

01:31:31.822 --> 01:31:33.349
And I was wrong.

01:31:35.150 --> 01:31:37.931
And my daughter,
she'd be lucky to have you.

01:31:45.614 --> 01:31:47.718
I'm not a quitter, Mr. Jones.

01:31:48.653 --> 01:31:50.791
I think I know that about you.

01:31:51.437 --> 01:31:52.963
Theresa doesn't.

01:31:54.413 --> 01:31:57.281
You just have to show her
what you're made of.

01:31:57.451 --> 01:32:00.647
You know she's hot-headed.
She's just like her mama.

01:32:04.461 --> 01:32:07.210
Every man gets to choose his destiny, son.

01:32:08.842 --> 01:32:10.981
No matter what his father did.

01:32:27.914 --> 01:32:30.152
And, Percy, you are not perfect.

01:32:30.379 --> 01:32:33.639
But that works for me because
two perfect people in one relationship...

01:32:33.705 --> 01:32:35.299
might be too much.

01:32:36.842 --> 01:32:39.175
And sometimes you bark
and bluff and bluster...

01:32:39.241 --> 01:32:42.241
but I always see the boy I married
25 years ago.

01:32:42.314 --> 01:32:46.307
And I only wish I loved him
as much as I did back then, but I don't.

01:32:51.497 --> 01:32:53.023
I love him more.

01:32:53.161 --> 01:32:55.265
Thank you, Marilyn. That was lovely.

01:32:55.464 --> 01:32:57.438
Percy? Your vows?

01:33:02.856 --> 01:33:04.286
Marilyn Jones.

01:33:04.967 --> 01:33:07.487
Everyone knows I didn't write my vows.

01:33:09.062 --> 01:33:12.062
Everyone knows because you kept
beating me up about it for weeks...

01:33:12.134 --> 01:33:15.006
crying to all your friends. You know?

01:33:15.624 --> 01:33:17.957
Now, look here, woman. I love you.

01:33:19.175 --> 01:33:21.924
But you didn't have to do me like that
about my vows.

01:33:21.990 --> 01:33:24.858
You know I don't like writing.
She knows that.

01:33:26.437 --> 01:33:28.129
I'm not a wordsmith.

01:33:28.839 --> 01:33:31.741
I do numbers. That's me. I don't do words.

01:33:32.485 --> 01:33:34.176
Damn it, I do money.

01:33:35.237 --> 01:33:38.881
And after 25 years, all I've asked you...

01:33:40.709 --> 01:33:42.368
is to let me be me.

01:33:46.756 --> 01:33:48.992
You'll never find

01:33:50.565 --> 01:33:52.605
As long as you shall live

01:33:53.029 --> 01:33:54.305
Oh, Lord.

01:33:54.532 --> 01:33:56.287
Someone to love you

01:33:56.356 --> 01:33:58.080
Love you, love you

01:33:58.149 --> 01:34:00.220
Tender like I do

01:34:00.291 --> 01:34:01.666
Tender like I do

01:34:01.731 --> 01:34:03.391
You know that about me, woman.

01:34:03.493 --> 01:34:05.728
You'll never find

01:34:07.331 --> 01:34:09.371
No matter where you search

01:34:09.443 --> 01:34:10.719
I'm not looking.

01:34:10.850 --> 01:34:12.738
Someone to care about you

01:34:12.802 --> 01:34:14.298
Care about you, care about you

01:34:14.372 --> 01:34:17.883
The way I do

01:34:19.555 --> 01:34:22.751
Oh, I'm not bragging on myself, baby

01:34:23.554 --> 01:34:27.581
But I'm the only one that loves you

01:34:29.890 --> 01:34:33.370
I think I forgot what love is
until you and Simon showed up.

01:34:33.441 --> 01:34:36.027
Give that man another chance, daughter.

01:34:36.577 --> 01:34:38.814
You'll never find

01:34:41.185 --> 01:34:42.331
Simon!

01:34:42.402 --> 01:34:43.929
Yes, Simon.

01:34:44.578 --> 01:34:47.447
It'll take the end of all time

01:34:48.224 --> 01:34:51.094
Someone who understands you

01:34:52.353 --> 01:34:54.971
Like I do

01:34:56.897 --> 01:34:58.456
That's not Jamal.

01:35:04.480 --> 01:35:08.854
I could probably find a million reasons
why we shouldn't be together.

01:35:09.311 --> 01:35:11.799
But you know what? I don't care.

01:35:13.792 --> 01:35:15.515
I don't care, either.

01:35:16.158 --> 01:35:17.500
I love you.

01:35:17.790 --> 01:35:20.092
And I'm sorry that I lied to you.

01:35:20.158 --> 01:35:21.466
I'm sorry, too.

01:35:23.869 --> 01:35:25.277
You're sorry?

01:35:26.846 --> 01:35:29.464
- Can you say that again?
- I'm sorry, Simon.

01:35:29.534 --> 01:35:32.119
You're sorry? She said she was sorry.
I believe she's...

01:35:32.189 --> 01:35:33.782
I'm sorry, Simon.

01:35:35.613 --> 01:35:38.199
- Get your man, girl!
- Go ahead, sweetie!

01:35:43.453 --> 01:35:45.656
Ladies and gentlemen,
it gives me great pleasure...

01:35:45.724 --> 01:35:49.718
to introduce to you all
my future son-in-law, Simon Green.

01:35:50.172 --> 01:35:53.400
He's broke, unemployed, and he's white.

01:35:54.269 --> 01:35:57.019
But he loves my Theresa
and that's all right with us.

01:35:57.084 --> 01:35:58.032
That's right.

01:35:58.460 --> 01:36:01.526
Welcome to the family, son.
Welcome to the family.

01:36:05.532 --> 01:36:07.156
And cue the magic.

01:36:14.396 --> 01:36:15.442
Look at this.

01:36:15.515 --> 01:36:17.522
Will you look at that shit?

01:36:18.266 --> 01:36:20.437
Drink up! Enjoy!

01:36:22.809 --> 01:36:24.216
Welcome, man.

01:36:41.114 --> 01:36:43.186
- Let's watch the tango.
- No, let's watch the party.

01:36:45.080 --> 01:36:48.309
- All right. Get your feet off the table.
- Sorry, sir.

01:36:53.239 --> 01:36:56.536
- I look pretty good out there.
- You do, Mom.

01:36:56.600 --> 01:37:00.309
Baby, you look so good
because you're twirling around me.

01:37:00.376 --> 01:37:02.678
Oh, yeah, there you go, there you go.

01:37:04.215 --> 01:37:05.776
All right, you blew that part.

01:37:05.847 --> 01:37:08.116
- That was perfect.
- There was hesitation there.

01:37:08.182 --> 01:37:10.551
- You did it better the night before.
- The night before?

01:37:10.615 --> 01:37:13.398
- What happened?
- We had a little dry run the night before.

01:37:13.464 --> 01:37:15.286
- Really?
- You didn't tell me that, Percy!

01:37:15.352 --> 01:37:18.612
You're hallucinating, Simon.
I ain't never danced with no man in my life.

01:37:18.678 --> 01:37:19.888
Taught him everything he knows.

01:37:19.958 --> 01:37:22.129
Percy Jones was born
knowing how to tango.

01:37:22.197 --> 01:37:24.467
And let me tell you something
about the tango.

01:37:24.534 --> 01:37:27.285
- It's a structured dance.
- I told you that.

01:37:32.215 --> 01:37:33.457
What was that, Mom?

01:37:33.525 --> 01:37:36.755
You know what that is, Theresa.
You're a grown-ass woman.

01:37:37.269 --> 01:37:39.919
- Damn, Mama, you still got it.
- I know it, Keisha.

01:37:39.989 --> 01:37:42.379
All right now, watch this.
This is when I got funky.

01:37:42.454 --> 01:37:46.642
- Go, Percy! It's your birthday!
- Go, Percy.

01:37:48.501 --> 01:37:49.678
- Let's watch the vows.
- No!

01:37:49.748 --> 01:37:52.681
- Watch the party.
- Okay, fine, whatever.

01:37:55.093 --> 01:37:57.645
- There you are.
- I got her, that girl is mine!

01:37:57.716 --> 01:38:00.400
I was just shocked you didn't fall down.

01:38:00.468 --> 01:38:01.580
That is cold.

01:38:01.653 --> 01:38:04.019
Look. Check me out. I am doing the hustle.

01:38:04.084 --> 01:38:06.222
I'm doing the hustle in your honor,
Percy Jones.

01:38:06.291 --> 01:38:08.843
That ain't no damn hustle.
That's the white man overbite.

01:38:08.914 --> 01:38:11.914
- You ain't even doing that right.
- Why's it gotta be a white thing?

01:38:11.987 --> 01:38:13.231
Blacks have overbites, too.

01:38:13.299 --> 01:38:16.266
- He's doing a great hustle!
- He's turning it up.

01:38:19.794 --> 01:38:21.997
- Why is my man looking at your ass?
- No, he's not.

01:38:22.065 --> 01:38:23.854
Why is your man Samoan?

01:38:23.921 --> 01:38:27.697
- Where is Manu these days?
- We broke up last week.

01:38:27.762 --> 01:38:30.063
- Thank you, Jesus.
- What happened?

01:38:30.130 --> 01:38:32.617
I only started going out with him
to mess with Daddy.

01:38:32.689 --> 01:38:36.105
And, girl, please. He is too big.
He is a bone crusher.

01:38:36.177 --> 01:38:37.867
- Watch your mouth!
- What?

01:38:37.937 --> 01:38:40.524
Do not use the word "bone" in my house.

01:38:50.929 --> 01:38:53.830
- Where were you all going?
- Let's see that again.

01:38:53.904 --> 01:38:56.622
Your mother and I
got a sudden thirst for punch.

01:38:56.784 --> 01:38:58.247
No. You're old enough to know.

01:38:58.320 --> 01:39:00.841
We going to shake some sheets.
Is that all right with you?

01:39:00.913 --> 01:39:03.530
I thought you said no bone in the house!

01:39:03.952 --> 01:39:04.967
No!

01:39:05.039 --> 01:39:07.973
If everyone wants to see the lift,
we do the lift.

01:39:08.046 --> 01:39:09.477
We're doing the lift!

01:39:09.551 --> 01:39:11.241
This is good.

01:39:11.311 --> 01:39:14.159
No. I was so sure
you were going to drop me there.

01:39:14.672 --> 01:39:15.751
I love you!

01:39:15.823 --> 01:39:18.670
This is Dirty Dancing.
I've been doing this since high school.

01:39:18.734 --> 01:39:19.782
Look at that.

01:39:19.855 --> 01:39:22.342
- Who's the man?
- You did it with other girls?

01:39:22.413 --> 01:39:25.677
No, I only do that with you.

01:39:28.974 --> 01:39:30.435
I know that hurt.

01:39:30.510 --> 01:39:33.705
See that move right there.
That's why you're not getting any grandkids.

01:39:33.773 --> 01:39:37.570
Let me call your mama right now
and thank her for those dance lessons.

01:39:37.645 --> 01:39:39.915
- That's a low blow.
- It's just a joke.

01:39:40.205 --> 01:39:42.888
- Simon!
- Come on. I'll catch your big ass.

01:39:47.021 --> 01:39:48.362
We're down!

01:39:49.677 --> 01:39:51.847
Good thing is, she didn't break that dress.

01:39:51.916 --> 01:39:54.667
No, she didn't,
but she felt bad about it all week.

01:39:55.020 --> 01:39:56.678
They gotta go deep.

01:39:56.780 --> 01:39:58.951
- I knew better.
- Oh, my God.

01:39:59.019 --> 01:40:01.322
- That was a great party.
- It was, Mom.

01:40:01.389 --> 01:40:04.486
Yeah, I guess a party not a party
till something get broke.

